body:
The test example has:

```
rpc_service MonsterStorage {
  Store(Monster):Stat (streaming: "none");
  Retrieve(Stat):Monster (idempotent);
}
```

Instead of "none", you can use "client", "server" or "bidi". This may not be documented.

There's no Go support yet.

@royalharsh has been porting my changes for C++ to work with Python, and I suggested Java and Go be next, see here: https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pulls?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Apr%20flatbuffers

(Also needs the corresponding work on the FlatBuffers side, see e.g. https://github.com/google/flatbuffers/commit/48f37f9e0a04f2b60046dda7fef20a8b0ebc1a70 )
